Name: Dilley Kerman

Date of Birth: 1/23/1997

Mission Details: RBD-MK6 is to launch at 5/13/2020 03:00. RBD-MK6 is to achieve stable orbit at 5/13/2020 03:20. We will figure out the rest later.

5/12/2020 16:32

My name is Dilley Kerman. I will be the first Kerbal to achieve a stable orbit around Kerbin, hopefully. It is the day before launch, I canÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t decide whether to be really excited or scared, all I know is that I canÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t keep my lunch down, the Scientists said that IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢d shouldnÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t eat too much anyway so I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t lose my lunch during launch.

5/13/2020 01:16

One hour before launch, I finally decided that IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m excited. I know I can trust the Scientists to get me there and back safely, even if they wonÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t tell me or anyone about the last flights. No matter, IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m still psyched for the flight, I will log again when IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m in orbit.

5/13/2020 03:43

That flight was exhilarating! From the ground to over 100,000 meters in just 10 minutes! Once at the Apoapsis the rocket burned to get into orbit though, it took a little longer to get in to orbit than I thought it would take. The rocket burned for a really long time for a normal orbit, I think something else is going on.

5/14/2020 18:57

IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m getting really far away from Kerbin. The Scientists just told me IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m now going to the Mun. I didnÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t get the chance to ask them what happened with the Ã¢â‚¬Å“go into orbit and comeback missionÃ¢â‚¬Â. But I guess itÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s out of my control.

5/17/2020 12:09

Is it really only 5/17? ItÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s felt like so much longer. There was never anything to do just floating though space so I didnÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t bother to log, but IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m logging today because the Mun is so close! I can see the individual craters itÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s so amazing! The Scientists told me they will start the engine burn to get into orbit at 12:30

5/17/2020 12:31

Why havenÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t the engines gone off? Why wonÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t the Scientist answer my calls? WhatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s going on?

5/18/2020 14:30

The Mun has finally left my sight. The Scientists called too they said IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m going burn at 5/20/2020 12:00 to achieve an orbit that intersects Minmus. An orbit around Kerbin, then the Mun, now Minmus, whatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s going on? Why does the mission keep changing? No matter, as long as IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m going home eventually. IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m going home right?

5/20/2020 12:45

That was a long burn; IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m kind of worried about the amount of fuel that could be remaining, but the Scientist said not to worry, so I shouldnÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t.

5/23/2020 14:09

I awoke to the sound of roaring engines. The Scientist didnÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t say anything about a burn. Had the engines malfunctioned? Or was something more sinister going on? I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t think I know where I am or where IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m going anymore.

5/23/2020 14:15

The engines stopped, it must have been a burn, or else IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m out of fuel and lost in space. I remember when I was excited for this, now IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m just terrified.

5/25/2020 16:56

The engines started again, nearly scared me too death, too bad it didnÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t. What is going on? I have been trying to contact the Scientists every hour since the last time the engines went off but thereÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s been no answer. I need to get too the bottom of this.

5/30/2020 18:32

The Scientists told me IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m going home! IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m so excited! They said IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m landing at 6/4/2020 only 5 more days in this prison!

6/5/2020 03:33

I never landed. The engines burned again. I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t know anything anymore.

6/17/2020 23:46

I no longer see Kerbin. All I have now are the stars and the Sun. I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t know what the Scientists are up too, and I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t think IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ll ever know. All I know is that I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t trust them anymore, nothing they have told me has been true and now IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m in the dark of space.

6/18/2020 00:30

The ship turned around and the engines burned. Then the stage separated and my little pod started a burn. What are they thinking I only have enough fuel to land with that!

6/18/2020 00:40

It stopped burning, probably because it is out of fuel. Where am I? What the hell are the Scientists doing? I hate them. I hate them, I hate them, I hate them. They wonÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t answer, they wonÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t say anything. All I can do is sit in this small pod and wait.

6/20/2020 13:13

The Scientist called today. They said my new home is Eve and I would be there eventually. Eventually? When was eventually? Tomorrow? Next week? Next month? Next year?

12/25/2020 01:25

Christmas. I miss Kerbin. But I did see Eve today, the Planet where all my hopes and dreams now lie, but the rocket didnÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t burn too get into orbit. What was the rockets name? I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t know anymore.

1/1/2021 00:00

Happy New Year. ItÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s not so happy though. IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ve been stuck in here so long, so long.

1/23/2021 03:56

Happy Birthday too me. IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m 24 now. I could care less, with no one to celebrate not even the Scientists called. I miss being with other Kerbals, I wouldnÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t mind a call from the Scientists. No. What am I thinking? I hate them. Hate them, hate them, hate them.

11/30/2021 08:45

I saw Eve again, still didnÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t land. IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m so lonely. I hate the Scientist. I get food from the machine. I sit. ThatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s all I know anymore. All I know.

1/1/2022 21:09

New Year. Nothing new though. I remember when I used to set New Year resolutions; I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t do that anymore, whatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s the point? WhatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s the point when all I have are the stars and the Sun? I havenÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t seen a planet in so long. I havenÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t seen my home since the launch day. ItÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s funny that seems so long ago; no it was long ago two years ago. I hate the Scientist. I hate this pod. I hate this suit. I hate the stars. I hate the Sun. I hate myself.

1/23/2022 07:12

ItÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s my Birthday. IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m 25. Why do I still do this dumb log? ItÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s only for the Scientists. I hate them.

12/31/2022 06:23

I saw Eve again. ItÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s so beautiful. So purple. ItÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s the only thing I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t hate anymore, itÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s my new home, and itÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s where I want to be. Not in this pod. Out In the vast oceans in a boat, in a comfy house on a purple hill, thatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s where I want to be.

1/1/2023 00:00

New Year.

1/23/2023 01:23

My Birthday again. IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m now 26. I want to go home, or I want to be on Eve, thatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s all I want.

1/1/2024 00:00

Another New Year. Too many years.

1/23/2025 05:18

IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m 27 now. Hooray.

1/1/2025 00:00

Another New Year. How long until I land? I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t want to wait any longer. I canÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t wait any longer. Why would they do this to me? Why, why, why, why, why? I hate them, thatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s why. I want to go home.

1/23/2025 09:00

I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t care for logs anymore.

11/23/2030 23:05

The Scientist contacted me they said they were going to start the landing sequence for Eve immediately. I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t trust them. But IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m so close to Eve, so close. Maybe I am landing. I hope I am land, I hope so much.

End Log
